## ğŸ§  Tips from the Trenches (10 Years of Failures)

- Always rinse grains **until water is clear**  
- Casing layer = natureâ€™s protective blanket  
- Bigger tubs = more success, more mushrooms  
- Donâ€™t touch your tub unless you absolutely must  
- Good light â†’ better pinning and growth  
- Watch the **smell** â€” earthy = good, sour = toss  
- Liner inside the tub prevents side pinning  
- Field capacity is a *feel*, not a number â€” squeeze test everything

